## What Is Session-RPE and How Is It Calculated?

RPE alone tells you how hard the session felt. But as a coach, you also care about **how long** the player worked at that intensity.

That‚Äôs where **session-RPE** comes in.

### The Session-RPE Formula

> **Session Load = RPE √ó Session Duration (minutes)**

This gives you a single number that represents the athlete‚Äôs **internal training load** for that session.

**Example (football training)**

- Session duration: 75 minutes
- Player‚Äôs RPE: 7 (‚Äúvery hard‚Äù)

> **Session Load = 7 √ó 75 = 525 AU**\
(AU = Arbitrary Units)

Now you can compare loads between:

- Different players in the same session
- Different sessions across the week
- Training sessions vs matches

All using the same simple metric.

Why is this powerful?

- It transforms a subjective feeling into a **quantified load value**.
- It makes **team sports load monitoring** possible even without external devices.
- It works across football training load, futsal conditioning, basketball practices, and more.

**Coach Takeaway:**\
**Session-RPE turns ‚Äúit felt hard‚Äù into a usable number.** That number becomes the foundation of your training load monitoring.

