## Common Mistakes When Using RPE and How to Avoid Them

Even though session-RPE is simple, there are common traps. Here are 6 mistakes and fixes.

### Mistake 1: Inconsistent Timing

#### Mistake

Sometimes asking right after training, sometimes an hour later.

#### Fix

Standardize: collect RPE **20‚Äì30 minutes post-session** every time.

**Coach Takeaway:**\
Consistency in timing = consistency in data.

---

### Mistake 2: Poor Athlete Education

#### Mistake

Athletes are never properly taught the scale, so they randomly pick numbers.

#### Fix

Spend time explaining the scale, give examples, and check their understanding early on.

**Coach Takeaway:**\
Invest one session in education, save months of low-quality data.

---

### Mistake 3: Using RPE as a ‚ÄúTest‚Äù of Toughness

#### Mistake

Players believe high RPE is ‚Äúgood‚Äù and low RPE is ‚Äúsoft‚Äù, so they bias responses.

#### Fix

Emphasize that RPE is **not a performance score**. It‚Äôs information to help manage load and protect them.

**Coach Takeaway:**\
RPE is about **honest communication**, not judgment.

---

### Mistake 4: Ignoring Context

#### Mistake

Interpreting a high RPE without considering heat, travel, stress, or recent matches.

#### Fix

When RPE is unexpectedly high or low, ask: ‚ÄúWhat could explain this today?‚Äù

**Coach Takeaway:**\
Numbers don‚Äôt replace coaching; they support better questions.

---

### Mistake 5: Not Combining RPE with Session Duration

#### Mistake

Looking only at the RPE number and not calculating **session load**.

#### Fix

Always multiply by duration to compare sessions and weeks accurately.

**Coach Takeaway:**\
**RPE √ó minutes** is what turns impressions into training load monitoring.

---

### Mistake 6: Collecting Data but Never Reviewing It

#### Mistake

Gathering RPE after every session, but never analyzing it.

#### Fix

Schedule a **weekly 15‚Äì20 minute review** to check player loads, weekly totals, and notable spikes.

**Coach Takeaway:**\
Your monitoring system is only as good as the decisions you make with it.

